    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>World Briefing | Europe: Norway: Amends For Nazi 'War Babies'</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Victor Homola (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Homola, Victor</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Norwegian Justice Ministry announces that war children, who were born to Norwegian mothers and Nazi fathers during World War II German occupation, will be compensated $3,000 to $30,000 for harassment they received after war (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The country's 8,000 to 12,000 ''war children'' -- born to Norwegian women and German soldiers during the German occupation in World War II -- will be compensated for the systematic harassment and bullying they were subjected to after the war, the Justice Ministry said. They will receive about $3,000 to $30,000. The amounts fall short of the claims of up to $72,000 sought by the Association of War Children.</p>
        <p>Victor Homola (NYT)</p>
      </block>
